      <p class="speaker__desc">Nathan has spent many-a-night trying to figure out how to most effectively accomplish his world domination plans and believes he has finally &ldquo;cracked the nut.&rdquo; Spoiler alert, the solution is &ldquo;use Ember.&rdquo; He recently signed up for a tour of duty with LinkedIn, accomplishing that which must seemingly be done at least once in a career: moving to the Silicon Valley. If you&rsquo;re bored ask Nathan about politics. You might still be bored, but at least there won&rsquo;t be that awkward silence anymore.</p>
      <div class="speaker__talk">
        <h3 class="speaker__talk__title">Building for Accessibility</h3>
        <p class="t-text">The advent of JavaScript applications means that we need to make sure we evolve our thinking on how to develop accessible experiences on top of the web platform. Just as we no longer design static visual experiences and instead plan for motion in our applications we also need to spend the same intentionality designing and building experiences for users of assistive technology.</p>
        <p class="t-text">You&rsquo;ll leave this talk with a few techniques you can bring to your applications tomorrow and hopefully a new approach to thinking about building web applications.</p>
      </div>
